The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | 2nd ODI highlights
                                                                                                                       7                                      2nd ODI highlights
                      
	 Sachin Tendulkar recorded his 46th century in ODIs. He now has 93 International hundreds including the 47 in Test cricket.         
	 It took 2962 ODIs and 1052 centuries before a player achieved 200 runs in a single innings in this format. Tendulkar is         
	The first player to score 200 in ODIs         
	The third player from the subcontinent to score 200-plus in List A matches         
	The ninth player overall to score 200-plus in List A matches         
	By scoring 25 fours Tendulkar now holds the record of most boundaries (4s) in a single innings. He bettered the previous record of 24 by Sanat Jayasuriya (157, vs Net at Amstelveen, 2006)         
	 Tendulkar (1859 runs) now has the most runs against South Africa in ODIs. He bettered the 1795 runs scored by Ricky Ponting.         
	 It was the ninth instance of the 400-run barrier being broken in ODIs and India (401/3) became the first side to have compiled three such scores. Following is the list:         
	 414/7 vs SL (Rajkot, 09-10)         
	 413/5 vs Ber (Port of Spain, 06-07)         
	 401/3 vs SA (Gwalior, 09-10)         
	COMPILED BY MOHANDAS MENON                                                                                                                     
